A fragment of a copper alloy socketed spearhead dating from the Middle or Late Bronze Age, about 1550 â€“ 800 BC. The object consists of the tip of the spearhead which has a pronounced central spine and a partial broken socket. The object also has partially retained wings which are missing large aspects and those retained are heavily abraded. An insufficient portion of the spear remains to prove diagnostic, therefore a specific type cannot be attributed, though it is probably comparable with the range of spearheads in Davis Groups 6-11.



The metal is a dark green with a heavily pitted and corroded patina.



Similar examples can be seen on the Portable Antiquities Database: Unique ID: GLO-F2F1FF, Unique ID: NARC-B41416, Unique ID: NLM-A82A87 and Unique ID: SUR-219BC8
